Introduction

D.O. is a South Korean singer, lyricist, and actor under Company Soosoo. He is a member of the boy group EXO and their subgroup EXO-K.

D.O. is well known for his sweet and clean vocals but he also received immense praise and public admiration when he started acting in the 2014 drama "It's Okay, That's Love" and the movie "Cart."

On July 1, 2019, D.O enlisted in the military as an active duty soldier. He was officially discharged on January 25, 2021.

He made his solo debut on July 26, 2021, with his first mini album "Empathy".
